The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 IN THE CITY

 The AIFF will bear all medical expenses for Deepak Mondal, who was injured during the Nehru Cup match against Bangladesh. Deepak suffered an injury on his left knee and was operated on by Dr Anant Joshi in Mumbai. 

 AIFF president Priya Ranjan Das Munshi on Tuesday met Deepak at his Salt Lake residence and promised full medical assistance to his treatment. The India defender is likely to miss action till December. 

 The 57th state athletic championships will see around 850 participants from 34 units vying for top honours at the Salt Lake Stadium from Thursday. South 24 Parganas have the biggest contingent of 105 in the four-day meet. 

 The BHA will celebrate the National Sports Day, commemorating Dhyan Chands 102nd birth anniversary, with a special film screening of Chak De India at a city multiplex on Wednesday afternoon for its players. This will be followed by the BHAs annual prize distribution ceremony at the Khudiram Anusilan Kendra. 

 The 18th state taekwondo meet will be held at the Khudiram Anusilan Kendra on Thursday and Friday. The winners will represent Bengal in the senior, junior and sub-junior nationals later this year. 

 BRIDGE: Inter-unit PSPB meet at Tollygunge Club

 DARTS: Inter-school meet at Assembly of God Church School

 GENERAL: National Sports Day celebrations at Khudiram Anusilan Kendra




